@reli3fxyz @andrwwang Later in the year I decided that what I wanted to do going forward was help folks get into web3, but there were two common turn-offs that needed addressing:

- The learning curve
- The prevalence of scammers, thieves, and otherwise bad actors

@reli3fxyz @andrwwang The Reli3f team quickly rallied a big group of A-list artists and raised $1m for Ukraine. Awesome!

But what made me choose them as my recipient was how much due diligence they're doing when deciding where the money goes.

https://t.co/fu4JhHla7B

@andrwwang @ArtMcArty @andrwwang I turned on notifications for you and this was the first one I got.

At first I thought the notification was you responding to the DM I sent you yesterday. When you read the DM you'll get why that was a confusing response for me.

(It's about relief for Ukraine)

@iKOR_OG @opensea I thought it was x2y2 at first, too. We'll find out more as the investigation continues.

What we do know is that the contract the thief used to collect sigs was deploy 30 days ago.

It's interesting OpenSea says it wasn't email phishing. That was the prevailing theory last night
